output: For each test case, print a line with the number asked in the specification.
input:
The input consists of many test cases.

The first line of a test case contains a single integer N, which represents the number of students, where 1 ≤ N ≤ 105.

The next N lines are the final ranking of the students. Each line contains a string with length 10.
name: Freshman Beats Veteran?
description: Professor Denis is curious to know if the final ranking of his N competitive programming students follows the registration order at the university. He asked your help to, given the final ranking, count how many (i, j) pairs exist such that i < j and m[i] > m[j], where 1 ≤ i,j ≤ N and m[i] means the registration of the student who got the i-th position.
